definitions.usage_example: He made up a story about why he was late.
definitions.alternative_example: He invented a story about why he was late.
definitions.usage_example_es: Él inventó una historia de por qué llegó tarde.

definitions.usage_example: They argued last night, but they made up.
definitions.alternative_example: They argued last night, but they reconciled.
definitions.usage_example_es: Discutieron anoche, pero hicieron las paces.

definitions.usage_example: She is in the bathroom making up her face.
definitions.alternative_example: She is applying cosmetics to her face.
definitions.usage_example_es: Ella está en el baño maquillándose la cara.

definitions.usage_example: This class is made up of 20 students.
definitions.alternative_example: This class is composed of 20 students.
definitions.usage_example_es: Esta clase está compuesta por 20 estudiantes.

definitions.meaning: Compensar (por algo malo o una falta)
definitions.usage_example: I'll make up for being late. I promise.
definitions.alternative_example: I'll compensate for being late. I promise.
definitions.usage_example_es: Compensaré por llegar tarde. Lo prometo.

definitions.usage_example: I saw them making out in the car.
definitions.alternative_example: I saw them kissing passionately in the car.
definitions.usage_example_es: Los vi besándose en el auto.

definitions.usage_example: It's too dark. I can't make out the license plate.
definitions.alternative_example: It's too dark. I can't discern the license plate.
definitions.usage_example_es: Está muy oscuro. No puedo distinguir la matrícula.

definitions.usage_example: What do you make of this email?
definitions.alternative_example: How do you interpret this email?

definitions.usage_example: When the rain started, we made for the house.
definitions.alternative_example: When the rain started, we went towards the house.
definitions.usage_example_es: Cuando empezó la lluvia, nos dirigimos a la casa.
